<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000003#     2#         3109#">Va. Code Ann. § 3.2-3109</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_3.2-3109"/><heading><desig>§ 3.2-3109.</desig><title>Form of accounts; annual audit</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The accounts and records of the Commission showing the receipt and disbursement of funds from whatever source derived shall be in such form as the Auditor of Public Accounts prescribes.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The accounts of the Commission shall be audited annually by the Auditor of Public Accounts, or his legally authorized representatives. Copies of the annual audit shall be distributed to the Governor and to the Chairmen of the House Committee on Appropriations and the Senate Committee on Finance.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="1999 VA CH 880"><content><span normalizedCite="1999 Va. Ch. 880">1999, cc. 880<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1999#000880#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1999 VA CH 962"><content><span normalizedCite="1999 Va. Ch. 962">962<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1999#000962#"/></l